Happy Thanksgiving to everyone!  Even if you don’t celebrate in your country let’s all be grateful for the people who come into and sadly sometimes leave our lives.  Be thankful for the impact and change they made for the better in us.  And I wanna take this time to say how thankful I am for all my fans.  All the support and love you’re showing me and all the  rangers through this tough time has been so heart warming. Thank you  for all the years of support you’ve shown.  Let’s just take a day to celebrate and tell EVERYONE we still have in our lives how much we love them.  I LOVE YOU! ❤️ Now, go get stuffed, you turkeys!  Enjoy! #thanksgiving  #love #powerrangers #family #ripjdf

@jdfffn is finally resting peacefully.  It was heartbreaking for us all seeing him buried.  But I was honored to be with the family at that moment. Damn.  Another one.  It’s heartbreaking seeing yet another piece of my childhood pass on.  As young as I feel, these past couple years have definitely shown me that on a long enough timeline, the survival rate for everyone is zero.  Now I don’t say that to bring everyone down.  I guess all I’m really saying is life is short for us here.  Embrace everything and everyone you hold dear.  And when we lose someone, carry on their memories inside you so they can live on.  Remember to tell people you love them.  I love all you guys.  And RIP Paul Reubens.  Thanks for making my childhood great.

This is a sad day indeed.  Can’t believe it’s been a year already.  Sometimes I forget and when something funny happens that we’d both enjoy, I say to myself “Man, I bet J would find this funny….I should text him..” and then I realize I can’t.  A moment of sadness washes back over me again.. You left too soon brother. Everyone (and I do mean EVERYONE) misses you.  Your light shines brighter than you ever knew.  We’re always gonna remember the funny, generous, mischievous soul that touched our lives for the past 30 years.  Hope you have peace and are resting well.

Heartbroken today. Yesterday we lost my niece Angela, my late brother’s daughter due to complications from pneumonia. It was sudden and everyone’s kind of in shock.  She was only in her early 30s. I miss the days when she was younger and we bonded listening to bands like Good Charlotte & Sum 41.  Definitely more innocent times. My heart goes out to her young boys and to her mother @bellcardenas I can’t imagine what you must be feeling at this moment.  May you rest in peace, Angela.  We love you.
